Measures and Tables 2

Now we need to write some DAX measures for specific columns
Below is each set of DAX code you will need and how to write it.

After you have completed all DAX entries you should be able to execute any step at your choosing

Steps

  1.  Right-click on countries-aggregated on the right-hand side underneath Fields and click "New measure"
  2.  Type into the bar the measures below that you will use for the Timeline visualization
  3.  You should have 4 measures in total 

Timeline (Measure)

.CA Confirmed = MAX('countries-aggregated'[Confirmed])
.CA Death= MAX('countries-aggregated'[Deaths])
.CA Recovered = MAX('countries-aggregated'[Recovered]) + 0
.CA Existing = [.CA Confirmed] - [.CA Death] - [.CA Recovered] + 0

    1. Click the data icon on the left side of the dashboard

     

    2. Click "New Table"

    3. Insert the formula below to get your Date table


    Calendar (Table)

    Date = 
    ADDCOLUMNS (
    CALENDAR (Date(Year(Min('countries-aggregated'[Date])),Month(Min('countries-aggregated'[Date])),
DAY(Min('countries-aggregated'[Date]))), Date(Year(Max('countries-aggregated'[Date])),
Month(Max('countries-aggregated'[Date])),DAY(Max('countries-aggregated'[Date])))),
    "Monthnumber", FORMAT ( [Date], "MM" ),
    "MonthYear", FORMAT ( [Date], "MMMYYYY" ),
    "Month", FORMAT ( [Date], "mmmm" ),
    "WeekNumber", "Week-"&WEEKNUM( [Date] ),
    "Week", WEEKNUM ( [Date]),
    "DayOfMonth", Month([DATE]) &"-"& FORMAT ( [Date], "dd" ),
    "YearQuarter", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY" ) & "/Q" & FORMAT ( [Date], "Q" ),
    "Year", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY" )
    )

    NOTE** Once the Calendar has been created it needs to be connected to the Date in 'countries-aggregated' table

    4. Click the model icon on the left side of the dashboard

    5. Click and drag Date from Date table just created to Date in countries-aggregated

    6. In the same model data view connect Name from WHO COVID-19 global table data January 15th 2021 at 4.53.55 AM to Country in countries-aggregated
